node.text:
If you haven’t heard this radio transmission, please take the time to listen. ⛔️Be cautioned it is hard to listen to.⛔️

The calm voice in the chaos  in Chicago during the incident that occurred on 8/7/2021. Thank you Dispatcher Keith Thornton - The way he took control of this incident and talked to his officers, kept his air completely shut down and clear, set a perimeter within seconds quite possibly is what resulted in the apprehension of the suspects. 

Dispatcher Keith Thornton was fast thinking and took initiative without any direction in the very beginning stages and ran the emergency like an actual incident commander - far beyond the criteria of any dispatcher. 

The world heard you loud and clear and we stand with you. 💙🖤💙🖤💙🖤💙
#chicago #dispatcherlife #policedispatcher #bluelivesmatter #chicagopolicedepartment #keiththorton #policeofficer #police #lawenforcement

node.text:
After COVID-Stricken Migrants Seen ‘Coughing, Sneezing’ at a Restaurant. 

HIDALGO COUNTY, Texas (CBSDFW.COM) – The La Joya Police Department issued a public health announcement after an officer approached an undocumented migrant family at Whataburger who told him Border Patrol released them because they had COVID-19.

On July 26 the police department of the small town along the Rio Grande and Mexican border shared details of the incident. They said a concerned citizen at the restaurant waved down the officer. The citizen told him about the family “coughing and sneezing without covering their mouths and not wearing face masks.” Whataburger management also told the officer that they wanted the group to leave as well due to “their disregard to other people’s health.”

node.text:
We know who’s to blame. Joe Biden and QueMala Harris decisions have enabled drug and human traffickers to make fortunes. The income potential from Biden’s willful neglect of our US Border is virtually unlimited as we can see here and who controls the human trafficking. 

Group of “Coyotes” [human traffickers] attack and threaten PNC Police Officers in San Mateo Ixtatán, Huehuetenango, Guatemala. PNC is The Policía Nacional Civil (Guatemala) - The police force of Guatemala

The recording allegedly was done on 7/21/21 and submitted online by a journalist from Guatemala. 

These Police Officers although armed with handguns allow themselves to be beaten and what appears their cell phones are taken from them. 

One of the police officers tries to escape but is chased down by the human smugglers. 

You can tell that there is/was some type of business negotiation happening or already happened between the police officers and the human smugglers, because they ask who put the finger? (Who told on us ~ then mention some type of raid, but it’s hard to understand)

Do not know if the police officers walked away from this as the video ends here. 

Hopefully the @pncdeguatemala PNC Police of Guatemala will look into this if they haven’t already. 

“Se nota que ahí hay negocio entre la PNC y los polleros, porque pregunta quién puso el dedo (se entiende que por una redada) y por eso no se defienden los policías, además se nota que hay un par de mexicanos. Los negocios de la PNC en todo el interior ojalá investiguen!!”

node.title: Group of Human Smugglers threaten and attack Guatemala Police Officers

node.text:
“It is time for Joe Biden to resign in disgrace for what he has allowed to happen to Afghanistan, along with the tremendous surge in COVID, the Border catastrophe, the destruction of energy independence, and our crippled economy,” Trump wrote in his Save America PAC on Sunday.

“It shouldn’t be a big deal, because he wasn’t elected legitimately in the first place!” he continued, blasting the administration.

Trump suggested Biden should resign after the Taliban quickly took control of Afghanistan, including the capital city of Kabul, endangering thousands of American citizens. Afghanistan’s own president, Ashraf Ghani, fled the country on Sunday.

node.text:
Here is your Saigon Moment Joe. 

PHOTO: Photo of Afghan civilians evacuated from Kabul airport by American forces on a military transport plane.

posted on the amn/nco/scno FB page that regularly posts info/photos from Airmen.

Pentagon has confirmed to White House Correspondent @jacquiheinrich that the Department of Defense is preparing to house thousands of Afghan refugees on American military installations, immediately including Fort McCoy in Wisconsin and Fort Bliss in Texas.

Documents obtained from a source show DoD planning to potentially relocate up to 30,000 Afghan SIV applicants into the United States in the immediate future.

“The situation in Afghanistan may lead to DoS [Department of State] allowing Afghan SIV applicants to be moved to temporary housing locations while still being vetted for parolee status,” the document reads.

“We want to have capacity to get up to several thousand immediately, and want to be prepared for potential of tens of thousands,” Pentagon Spox John Kirby tells me. “Bliss & McCoy have capability right now – what’s advantageous is w/ a bit of work, could increase in short order.”

Kirby says American citizens will not be given priority evacuation over Afghan SIV applicants. “Once we get more airlift out of Kabul, we’re going to put as many people on those planes as we can. There will be a mix...

not just American citizens, but perhaps some Afghan SIV applicants as well. We’re going to focus on getting people out of the country, then sorting it out at the next stop. It’s not going to be just Americans first, then SIV applicants," Kirby tells me.

Full thread is posted on twitter via @jacquiheinrich

node.text:
Biden abandoned Trump’s peace plan and exit strategy and haphazardly created his OWN. Biden is FULLY responsible for this absolute catastrophic wreck. 

President Joe Biden ordered the withdrawal of US forces from Afghanistan over the advice of some of his senior-most advisers in the Pentagon and State Department, leaders who are now charged with carrying out the particulars of the complicated drawdown.

Multiple current and former officials tell CNN that those advisers -- including Chairman of the Joint Chiefs Gen. Mark Milley, leader of US Central Command Gen. Frank McKenzie and some State Department officials -- expressed concerns about what a full withdrawal might mean for the US counter-terror mission. They also expressed concern about the security of US diplomats based there.

Warnings about the potential for the Taliban to regain power and for violence to increase pervaded the numerous meetings over the past few months, according to officials, though Biden continually chafed at suggestions US troops should remain in Afghanistan for much longer, according to people familiar with the matter, reminding his advisers that -- like his two predecessors -- he promised voters he would end the country's longest war, even if that meant going against the recommendations of his top generals.

"All relevant points of view were heard and all arguments were put on the table," said one senior administration official who spoke to CNN on condition of anonymity.

Still no word from Joe Biden. Kamala Harris has reportedly refused comment. 

[Harris was reportedly pressed to give an update on Afghanistan to the American people but refused.

node.text:
[The Biden administration is now saying  American citizens will not be given priority evacuation over Afghan SIV applicants. This is according to a statement made by Pentagon Press Secretary John Kirby made to @jacquiheinrich ] 

Reportedly happening now; All commercial flights are suspended at Hamid Karzai International Airport in Kabul, a statement reads. The statement calls on the people to avoid crowds at the airport. ~ @tolonewsofficial 

Joe Biden and Kamala Harris had MONTHS to put together a list of VETTED US aligned persons, who would need to be evacuated in case of the fall of the Afghan government. Joe went against the advice of his security team, but someone should have done this; someone should have done their phuking job, right? 

Pentagon has confirmed to White House Correspondent @jacquiheinrich that the Department of Defense is preparing to house thousands of Afghan refugees on American military installations, immediately including Fort McCoy in Wisconsin and Fort Bliss in Texas.

Documents obtained from a source show DoD planning to potentially relocate up to 30,000 Afghan SIV applicants into the United States in the immediate future.

“The situation in Afghanistan may lead to DoS [Department of State] allowing Afghan SIV applicants to be moved to temporary housing locations while still being vetted for parolee status,” the document reads.

“We want to have capacity to get up to several thousand immediately, and want to be prepared for potential of tens of thousands,” Pentagon Spox John Kirby tells me. “Bliss & McCoy have capability right now – what’s advantageous is w/ a bit of work, could increase in short order.”

Kirby says American citizens will not be given priority evacuation over Afghan SIV applicants. “Once we get more airlift out of Kabul, we’re going to put as many people on those planes as we can. There will be a mix...

not just American citizens, but perhaps some Afghan SIV applicants as well. We’re going to focus on getting people out of the country, then sorting it out at the next stop. It’s not going to be just Americans first, then SIV applicants," Kirby tells me.

Full thread is posted on twitter via @jacquiheinrich
